1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
Most productivity apps help us do more.
My problem is the opposite.

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:10,000
I’m Yoshie Yamada, a novelist and freelance writer,

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:15,000
and Maybe Tomorrow. asks whether one more worthwhile thing
really belongs today.

4
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:21,000
I name one activity and answer seven scored questions,
plus one final check about making it smaller.

5
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:28,000
The rules are fixed and transparent,
with only three possible verdicts—

6
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:35,000
no generated advice and no hidden confidence score.

7
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:41,000
On an overfull day, another side project gets “Maybe tomorrow.”

8
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:47,000
The app checks all 78,125 scored answer combinations

9
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:54,000
and shows the smallest facts that would have changed the result,
without changing my answers.

10
00:00:54,000 --> 00:01:01,000
Calendar context is optional. I can import an ICS file,
a Google Calendar export ZIP,

11
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:07,000
or use this fictional sample.
Everything stays in this browser.

12
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:13,000
The app reads time, but only I decide which events must stay,
can move or shrink,

13
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:20,000
take energy, or protect recovery.

14
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:26,000
For one more hour of writing,
it searches only changes I have authorized.

15
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:32,000
Here, shortening the fictional gym creates a continuous hour.

16
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:39,000
Fixed commitments and recovery stay protected,
and the source calendar is never edited.

17
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:45,000
I did not manually write or edit the application code.

18
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:51,000
I shaped the product with my AI partner, Templex Tsukino,
using GPT-5.6 Sol.

19
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:58,000
Templex turned our conversations into signed specifications,
rules, copy, privacy boundaries, and review gates.

20
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:04,000
Codex implemented, tested, documented,
and deployed the React app.

21
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:12,000
I directed part of the build from my phone
at an internet cafe and a gym,

22
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:19,000
then tested the product and approved the release.

23
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:25,000
Maybe Tomorrow. was built through AI collaboration,
but it refuses to pretend AI understands your life.

24
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:30,000
No AI reads your calendar. We can see the time.
Only you know what it means.
